<paragraph id="E44CEB00FFF2772BFF14FA4DFF4CF98D" blockId="1.[151,1436,1478,2016]" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">
This species has previously been synonymized with 
<taxonomicName id="23F39083FFF2772BFD6FFA43FF00FA19" authority="Gravenhorst" authorityName="Gravenhorst" box="[748,1092,1478,1503]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Bassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="annulatus">
<emphasis id="D6873712FFF2772BFD6FFA43F8F5FA19" box="[748,945,1478,1503]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">Bassus annulatus</emphasis>
Gravenhorst
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="23F39083FFF2772BFBFEFA43FED3FA19" authority="Thomson" authorityName="Thomson" box="[1149,1431,1478,1503]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Bassus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deletus">
<emphasis id="D6873712FFF2772BFBFEFA43FE66FA19" box="[1149,1314,1478,1503]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">Bassus deletus</emphasis>
Thomson
</taxonomicName>
, but actually represents a distinct species (
<emphasis id="D6873712FFF2772BFDEDFA60F990F9C4" bold="true" box="[622,724,1515,1539]" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">stat. rev.</emphasis>
). It has been reported from the Western Palaearctic region and from 
<collectingCountry id="9CE4AB90FFF2772BFF55F985FA4BF9E1" box="[214,271,1550,1574]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">India</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="806296F1FFF2772BFEA3F985FA94F9E1" author="Yu" box="[288,464,1550,1574]" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" refString="Yu, D. S., van Acherberg, C. &amp; Horstmann, K. (2005) World Ichneumonoidea 2004 - Taxonomy, Biology, Morphology and Distribution. Taxapad CD / DVD. www. taxapad. com, Vancouver, Canada." type="book" year="2005">
Yu et al., 
<number id="523BF927FFF2772BFE10F985FA94F9E1" box="[403,464,1550,1574]" pageId="1" pageNumber="36" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). I here provide a diagnosis and short description which are based on the Mongolian specimen and on additional specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="9CE4AB90FFF2772BFD09F9B8F9A9F98C" box="[650,749,1587,1611]" name="Hungary" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">Hungary</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="9CE4AB90FFF2772BFD7BF9B9F83AF98D" box="[760,894,1586,1610]" name="Switzerland" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">Switzerland</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="9CE4AB90FFF2772BFC37F9B8FF40F98D" box="[948,1028,1587,1610]" name="France" pageId="1" pageNumber="36">France</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
